# OnlyTwins Core

Production AI content generation platform. Not a demo.

## Stack
- Next.js 16 App Router, React 19, TypeScript (strict)
- Supabase Auth + Postgres (RLS) + Storage
- Stripe subscriptions + webhooks
- RunPod serverless GPU workers
- Vercel deployment (GitHub main → auto-deploy)
- Tailwind CSS v4, Framer Motion

## Hard rules — never violate
- Never break billing (checkout → webhook → subscription provisioning)
- Never break auth/session handling
- Never break webhook idempotency — `stripe_webhook_events` insert must come first
- Never invent schema columns — read `supabase/migrations/` before writing DB code
- Never write to `subscriptions` table except from `app/api/billing/webhook/route.ts`
- Never expose `supabase-admin.ts` (service role) to client-side code
- Keep admin UX completely separate from customer UX
- No dead UI or placeholder flows
- No technical language exposed to customers
- Prefer modifying existing flows over creating parallel ones

## Customer routes (admins redirected away from these)
`/`, `/dashboard`, `/vault`, `/billing`, `/me`, `/requests`, `/subjects`,
`/creator`, `/library`, `/training-vault`, `/upload`, `/onboarding/**`

## Protected routes (require session)
`/upload`, `/admin/**`

## Middleware
`proxy.ts` — single file, all routing + security headers + rate limiting + admin redirect.
Do not add routing logic anywhere else in middleware.

## Admin detection
`lib/admin.ts` → `isAdminUser(userId, email)` — checks `ADMIN_OWNER_EMAILS` env var.
Called in `proxy.ts`, `app/admin/layout.tsx`, and `app/auth/callback/page.tsx` (via `/api/admin/session`).

## Auth callback
`app/auth/callback/page.tsx` — client component.
After session: POST `/api/thank-you/complete` → GET `/api/admin/session` → route to `/admin` or `next` param.

## Generation engine flag
`lib/generation-engine.ts` → `isGenerationEngineEnabled()` — checks `GENERATION_ENGINE_ENABLED=true`.
All generation entry points must check this first. Returns 503 if disabled.

## Service creator
`lib/service-creator.ts` → `getServiceCreatorId()` — platform's canonical creator ID.
Used as `creator_id` for all done-for-you plan subscriptions.

## Cron schedule (UTC)
| Time | Path |
|---|---|
| 8am | `/api/cron/daily-lead-scrape` |
| 9am | `/api/cron/enqueue-lead-samples` |
| 10am | `/api/cron/send-outreach` |
| 12pm | `/api/cron/process-customer-generation` — `processPendingCustomerGeneration(admin, 25)` |
| Midnight | `/api/cron/monthly-customer-generation` — `scheduleMonthlyCustomerBatches` + process 25 |

All cron routes verify `Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>`.

## Deployment
- Push to `main` → Vercel auto-deploys
- Schema changes: run SQL migration in Supabase **before** pushing dependent code
- Always include: SQL required? New env vars? Rollback plan? Test steps?
- See `docs/deployment.md`
